﻿
        <h2>What Monday Night Meant</h2>
﻿
        <p>We started PowerUP in 2017 with a simple observation: martial arts senseis are professional mentors. They show up week after week for the same kids. They teach discipline and respect before they teach technique. They build relationships that last years.</p>
﻿
        <p>What Dr. Lakes gave us Monday night was the vocabulary to say what we&rsquo;ve always known to be true: the thing we&rsquo;re building in these kids isn&rsquo;t a karate skill. It&rsquo;s a life skill &mdash; one that will affect their health, their finances, their relationships, and their communities for decades to come.</p>
﻿
        <p>A room full of Atlanta&rsquo;s most accomplished people sat quietly and listened. That felt meaningful.</p>
﻿
        <p>If you&rsquo;d like to learn more about PowerUP &mdash; or if you&rsquo;re ready to put a child on that path &mdash; we&rsquo;d love to hear from you. <a href="../donate.html">Join us in continuing this work.</a></p>
﻿
